{title: Two Hearts Deep In The Blues}
{artist: Hank Thompson}
{composer: Written by Hank Thompson and Lyle Gaston}

[G]I found you sitting there [D7]about to cry
And so was I she just gave me the [G]news
I could tell that you were [D7]just like me in misery
Two hearts deep in the [G]blues

And so we sit and talked the [D7]whole night through
And then I knew that I could never [G]refuse
Your heart was aching from a [D7]broken trust
And we were just two hearts deep in the [G]blues

Do you [C]remember that you told me
All of your [G]love deserted you
Do you [C]remember that I told you
We were [G]both in the same [D7]canoe

[G]Two broken hearts were somehow [D7]blended then
And mended when we each had nothing to [G]lose
So we took the chance [D7]and aren't glad
Because we had two hearts deep in the [G]blues

Repeat #3,4